For the past two years i'm been fixated on my past relationship with my ex. But throughout the two years I've grown a lot personally - built better friendships, became more mature and less anxious, built a better foundation in God and as a Christian. I realised I was probably a terrible gf with lots of insecurities - I was quite immature and had anxiety at that time (due to circumstances like social circles and my stressful job). 

&amp;#x200B;

Over the course of time, I've gotten better and started moving forward. Sometimes I wake up thinking of the past, but I've decided to start actively moving forward! :) I've dealt with my anxiety, and left a stressful job that was causing a lot of anxiety, quit instagram and all the toxic/gossipy social circles. Life is much better and simpler and healthier. 

&amp;#x200B;

But, I completely stopped flirting and bantering with people for the 2 years, and lost a lot of confidence in myself. I look at other 26 year olds around me and they have got their lives altogether - married, in stable relationships or rocking their personalities. 

&amp;#x200B;

**For people who are confident - any tips for me? :D** I'm still quite shaky and awkward sometimes, and would love more of my own character! I used to be fun and banter and be confident around my ex, but I'm scared sometimes that people won't like my true character.

