Hi all, I don't post much about myself, but this just crossed my mind and thought maybe it would interest someone out there.

&amp;#x200B;

A few years back, it dawned on me how often I thought of something good I wanted to do, but didn't do because I was overthinking it, and by the time I thought about it, it was over. Mostly small things: opening doors, offering a quick hand, etc. I live in an urban area, and this comes up a lot (it could also bite you in the ass).

&amp;#x200B;

I made a rule that if I thought of something good to do and caught myself overthinking it, then I would literally turn around and do it. I'm making progress. The very first thing to happen was at work in a social setting, where we were sitting in a group, and there was a girl sitting alone, so I asked her if she wanted to join us. The old me would have reasoned that if she wanted to join, she would. But that doesn't mean I shouldn't ask.

&amp;#x200B;

I kept at it and I can feel myself becoming a little truer and freer. I was already pretty comfortable in my skin, but now I feel liberated. Most notably, I watched a pretty bad hit and run, so I notified a nearby meter maid (whose department it clearly was not so he didn't do anything), and I took pictures, went to the restaurant I was going to, and asked them for a pen and paper so I could go back and leave a note saying they could email me for them. I hope it helped in some way.

&amp;#x200B;

What inspired me was once I was driving with a coworker (older than me), and out of nowhere, he said, "That guy just hit that lady!" and he got out of the car and sprinted down almost a whole block including crossing the intersection to break it up (turns out it was two guys hah). But man, I want to be like that. Screw everything else. In that moment, you realize nothing else about him mattered except that he wanted to do the right thing.

&amp;#x200B;

I don't really have any good closure for this, but I hope someone found this interesting. I want more people to be like the good people I've met and the good person I'm trying to be.

